RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 26 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $7,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRONIT was sent from the one post position, secured the inside trip, set the pace, lead all the way around the turn, was asked at the quarter pole and drew off. Much the best today. PAT HAND GIRL settled far off the pace early in the three path, gained ground after the half, circled around in the turn, was five wide in lane and closed gaining ground bit by bit and out finished the rest. SUNSHINE STAR settled just off the leaders hip, was in a set of three for the first half of the race, shook one of those competitors after the half, had sights on the leaders at the quarter, launched a drive and was caught late but was up for third. THE MISSING PIECE broke out at the start causing an outside foe to break out as well, was corrected, raced mid pack but never fired. FLASHYBOY'S LILSIS was pushed out at the start by the horse to her inside, was given time to find her stride, chased from the back, swung wide at the quarter but had no impact. WENDY WILECAT vied for the early lead from the seven path, settled in the second tier from the outside, angled towards the rail at the quarter pole and stopped in the lane. RESPOSADO sent in between horses in the second tier, was in contention at the three eighths pole, was shifted out of traffic before the quarter mile pole and was eased in the lane. RESPOSADO DID WALK OFF.

ENTRY.NAME: Ironit
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail, pace, never challenged, much the best.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BERNIECE broke in and bumped a rival at the start, stalked behind the top pair while a bit off of the rail around the turn, bid for the lead inside of them in upper stretch, and drove clear at the furlong grounds. RUN DREAMING bumped inner rival at the start, dueled for the lead inside of a foe while in the two path, but was outkicked by a rail bidder approaching midstretch, flopped back to his left lead in the final furlong, and lasted for place from an inner rival. BITSY PERFECTMATCH lacked speed along the inside, but was keen inside of rivals leaving the half mile pole, steadied into the turn, took the bend in the three path, shifted out to the five path in upper stretch, and rallied through the final furlong, but failed to catch an outer rival for place. PERIPHERAL VISION pursued from midpack two wide early on, chased along the inside around the turn, and kept on evenly. DIVINE DEFENCE was bumped an bothered by an outer rival at the start, dueled for the lead outside of a rival while in the three path, but gave way nearing midstretch. SWEET LITTLE ROSE was fractious in the gates, broke a step slow, trailed in the four path around the turn, shifted out in upper stretch, and lacked a rally. CUSTOMIZED TWIN hopped slightly before being bumped and bothered by an outer rival at the start, tracked four wide, and gave way in the six path through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JACK A ROSE showed good early speed, was able to take command of the race early, comfortably attended the pace, and responded to steady urging down the lane with a determined finish. HE'S GOT THIS left the gates and easily ended up on the front end from the four path, took back a bit and settled in hands down the backside, moved closer to the rail while saving ground, stayed within striking distance while still being relaxed, was asked after the three eighths pole and willingly responded, continued to gain ground at the eighth mile pole was asked for an all out run and responded gamely but needed more room. FIELDSTONE was well back early, saved ground from the rail, was urged to catch up around the half, split horses at the five eighths pole, continued through the turn but flattened out in the lane. BONUS APPRECIATION was off a step slow, raced from the three path through the first turn while passing another rival, angled back to the rail and saved ground, starting moving at the half mile pole, made short work out of catching up, while still on the rail, cut the corner and came down the lane while still gaining momentum, aimed for the leader but just had too much to make up but raced gamely. MILLARD'S SMILE raced off the pace from the five path and had no impact. CRIMINAL DEFENSE was never involved. CLARESTOWN vied for the early lead, stayed on and matched strides with the other horse on the front from the three path and faded down the lane.
